'''''Young Jedi Knights: Darkest Knight''''' is a [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] young-adult novel written by [[Kevin J. Anderson]] and [[Rebecca Moesta]]. It is the fifth book in the ''[[Star Wars: Young Jedi Knights]]'' series, and it was first published by [[Berkley Boulevard]] in [[June]] [[1996]].

The novel was reprinted in ''[[Young Jedi Knights: The Rise of the Shadow Academy]]'' (1996) and ''[[Young Jedi Knights: Jedi Sunrise]]'' ([[2003]]).

==Plot summary==
[[Lowbacca|Lowie]] is concerned for his sister, [[Sirrakuk|Sirra]], who is about to undergo a dangerous [[Wookiee/Legends|Wookiee]] rite a passage. Lowie returns to [[Kashyyyk/Legends|Kashyyyk]], accompanied by [[Darth Caedus|Jacen]], [[Jaina Solo Fel|Jaina]]and [[Tenel Ka Djo|Tenel Ka]]. When the [[Second Imperium]] learns of this, Master [[Brakiss]] dispatches [[Zekk]] and a team of [[Dark Jedi/Legends|Dark Jedi]] to lead a raid on [[Thikkiiana City/Legends|Thikkiiana City]], a major exporter of [[Computer/Legends|computer]] technology, to [[Thief/Legends|steal]] vital computer parts. By executing this mission, he will fulfill his great potential and win the title of the [[Darkest Knight]] of the Second Imperium. As a test of his loyalty, Zekk is also tasked with [[Death/Legends|slaying]] his former friends should they cross paths. The Second Imperium attacks Kashyyyk, and the young [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] are chased through the lower levels of the treacherous [[Jungle/Legends|jungles]]. Zekk and Jaina confront each other, but Zekk cannot bring himself to harm her. He lets her go, warning her that [[Yavin 4/Legends|Yavin 4]] will soon be under attack. Zekk informs his colleagues that he killed Jaina. Meanwhile, the [[Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] arrives at the [[Shadow Academy]]. Much to the consternation of Brakiss, he is not allowed to see or speak to [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]]. But the Emperor remotely orders Brakiss to set course for Yavin 4.

==Release and reception==
A special charity auction for the original annotated manuscript of this book started in [[November]] [[2013]]. The manuscript included editorial and production marks, different word choices and continuity alterations. The auction ended on [[December 5]], 2013.<ref name="http://roqoodepot.com/2013/11/23/young-jedi-knights-darkest-knight-original-manuscript/">''[http://roqoodepot.com/2013/11/23/young-jedi-knights-darkest-knight-original-manuscript/ Roqoo Depot]''</ref>

==Continuity==
[[Anakin Solo]] is mistakenly referred to as [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] in chapter two.

